<TITLE> NRB conference eyes 'nation building' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 1 (bdnews24.com)A three-day NRB conference on manpower development kicks off Thursday with the aim of exploring "a new approach to nation building", say its organisers. The conference will include at least ten seminars, to be attended by government ministers, bureaucrats, expatriate academics and entrepreneurs, touching on issues such as rights of workers at home and abroad, role of government agencies in safeguarding those rights and ways to further develop the country's human resources. President Zillur Rahman is expected to inaugurate the 'First NRB Manpower Development & Opportunities Conference 2009', co-organised by Scholars Bangladesha network of non-resident Bangladeshisand the Dhaka-based Human Capital Development Limited, at the Sheraton Hotel. The conference will conclude with an awards ceremony, to be attended by finance minister AMA Muhith, Scholars Bangladesh chairman ME Chowdhury Shamim told a press conference Wednesday. Four awards will be given in the categories of Innovation in Remittance Collection, Migration Sector Development, Best Institute for Trade Skilled Development and Best Recruiting Agency.
